We do not train to be merciful here.
Mercy is for the weak.

15
00:00:36,538 --> 00:00:41,126
Here, on the street, in competition,
a man confronts you, he's the enemy.

16
00:00:41,626 --> 00:00:45,171
An enemy deserves no mercy.
What is the problem, Mr. Lawrence?

17
00:00:48,425 --> 00:00:50,802
Class, we have visitors.

18
00:00:57,475 --> 00:01:00,353
I hear you jumped
some of my students last night.

19
00:01:00,645 --> 00:01:02,772
Afraid the facts mixed up.

20
00:01:03,231 --> 00:01:06,734
Now you get your boy on the mat
or you and I will have a major problem.

21
00:01:06,818 --> 00:01:09,279
Too much advantage, your <i>dojo</i>.

22
00:01:10,864 --> 00:01:12,365
Name a place.

23
00:01:12,949 --> 00:01:14,367
Tournament.

24
00:01:15,785 --> 00:01:17,996
Come on, Johnny, kill him!

25
00:01:21,416 --> 00:01:23,877
<i>Point! Chop! That's two for LaRusso!</i>

26
00:01:24,919 --> 00:01:26,588
Time out, time out.

27
00:01:26,796 --> 00:01:29,048
Go to your <i>sensei</i>. Turn. Kneel.

28
00:01:29,674 --> 00:01:31,926
Hey, Johnny, you're a cream-puff!

29
00:01:33,511 --> 00:01:35,054
Sweep the leg.

30
